18:26.005 --> 18:27.606
HEATING.

18:27.606 --> 18:29.241
FOR A LOW-INCOME FAMILY, THOUGH,

18:29.241 --> 18:31.077
THEY SPEND MAYBE 10% TO 15% OF

18:31.077 --> 18:32.578
THEIR INCOME ON HOME HEATING,

18:32.578 --> 18:34.180
AND THE REASON IS SIMPLE: THEY

18:34.180 --> 18:35.881
JUST HAVE LESS MONEY.

18:35.881 --> 18:37.817
SO THAT, IF YOU'RE POOR, IT

18:37.817 --> 18:38.651
DOESN'T MEAN YOU USE LESS

18:38.651 --> 18:39.785
ENERGY; YOU STILL HAVE A HOUSE

18:39.785 --> 18:40.820
TO HEAT.

18:40.820 --> 18:41.921
AND IF ANYTHING, YOUR HOUSE

18:41.921 --> 18:43.422
MIGHT BE OLDER, MIGHT BE

18:43.422 --> 18:44.357
LEAKY.

18:44.357 --> 18:45.958
SO, YOUR BILL IS VERY HIGH

18:45.958 --> 18:47.593
RELATIVE TO INCOME, WHERE, FOR A

18:47.593 --> 18:49.095
MIDDLE-INCOME FAMILY, IT'S MUCH

18:49.095 --> 18:50.162
LOWER.

18:50.162 --> 18:51.597
SO, WE THINK ABOUT HOME ENERGY,

18:51.597 --> 18:53.299
YOU HAVE TO THINK ABOUT JUST THE

18:53.299 --> 18:54.767
BURDEN IT PLACES ON POOR

18:54.767 --> 18:56.502
FAMILIES TO STAY CONNECTED TO

18:56.502 --> 18:58.404
THE GRID AND TO CONTINUE TO BUY

18:58.404 --> 18:59.572
HOME HEATING OIL.

18:59.572 --> 19:00.706
AND THE PROBLEM IS THAT THE

19:00.706 --> 19:03.509
ENERGY ASSISTANCE PROGRAM HAS

19:03.509 --> 19:06.412
BEEN CUT FROM $5.1 BILLION IN

19:06.412 --> 19:10.116
2010 TO ABOUT $3.3 BILLION NOW.

19:10.116 --> 19:11.584
SO, WE'VE LOST CLOSE TO $2

19:11.584 --> 19:14.787
BILLION IN ASSISTANCE TO HELP

19:14.787 --> 19:15.588
FAMILIES.

19:15.588 --> 19:16.255
>> Srennivasan: BESIDES THE

19:16.255 --> 19:17.423
NORTHEAST OR THE MIDWEST, ARE

19:17.423 --> 19:19.291
PLACES, SAY, FOR EXAMPLE, IN

19:19.291 --> 19:20.793
THE DEEP SOUTH WORSE OFF BECAUSE

19:20.793 --> 19:21.794
THEY DON'T NECESSARILY HAVE THE

19:21.794 --> 19:22.561
INFRASTRUCTURE, THEY DON'T

19:22.561 --> 19:23.896
PREPARE FOR IT LIKE THE

19:23.896 --> 19:25.564
NORTHEAST DOES?

19:25.564 --> 19:26.265
>> WELL, IT'S A LITTLE BIT

19:26.265 --> 19:26.766
DIFFERENT.

19:26.766 --> 19:28.234
HERE'S WHAT HAPPENS.

19:28.234 --> 19:29.001
YOU KNOW, THERE'S FEDERAL

19:29.001 --> 19:30.369
FUNDING THAT'S SORT OF BASE

19:30.369 --> 19:32.972
FUNDING, WE CALL IT.

19:32.972 --> 19:34.373
AND THEN, STATES' UTILITIES

19:34.373 --> 19:36.075
ADD MONEY TO THAT.

19:36.075 --> 19:37.476
MOST OF THE EXTRA MONEY THAT'S

19:37.476 --> 19:39.311
ADDED TO ENERGY ASSISTANCE IS IN

19:39.311 --> 19:40.146
THE NORTHEAST AND MIDWEST

19:40.146 --> 19:41.047
STATES.

19:41.047 --> 19:42.748
ALSO IN THOSE STATES, THEY HAVE

19:42.748 --> 19:44.417
VERY STRONG SHUTOFF PROTECTION.

19:44.417 --> 19:45.451
SO, YOU FALL BEHIND IN YOUR

19:45.451 --> 19:47.453
BILL, SAY, IN MASSACHUSETTS,

19:47.453 --> 19:48.487
YOU CAN'T BE SHUT OFF.

19:48.487 --> 19:50.256
IT'S A PUBLIC HEALTH CONCERN.

19:50.256 --> 19:51.624
AS YOU GO SOUTH, ESPECIALLY

19:51.624 --> 19:52.758
THE SOUTHERN STATES AND THE

19:52.758 --> 19:54.393
WESTERN STATES, THERE REALLY

19:54.393 --> 19:55.795
ARE NO SHUTOFF PROTECTIONS

19:55.795 --> 19:57.163
OR THEY'RE MUCH WEAKER.

19:57.163 --> 19:58.364
SO, IF YOU'RE A LOW-INCOME

19:58.364 --> 20:00.766
FAMILY, SAY, IN NORTH CAROLINA,

20:00.766 --> 20:01.834
IT'S MUCH HARDER.

20:01.834 --> 20:02.868
YOU FALL BEHIND IN YOUR BILL,

20:02.868 --> 20:04.036
THE STATE HAS LESS MONEY TO

20:04.036 --> 20:04.970
WORK WITH.

20:04.970 --> 20:06.072
THERE IS FEWER UTILITY

20:06.072 --> 20:07.273
SUPPORTS, AND THEY'RE MORE

20:07.273 --> 20:08.874
LIKELY TO GET INTO A SHUTOFF

20:08.874 --> 20:10.843
SITUATION OR FALL FURTHER BEHIND

20:10.843 --> 20:11.811
IN THEIR BILL BECAUSE THERE'S

20:11.811 --> 20:12.912
JUST LESS MONEY TO HELP THEM

20:12.912 --> 20:13.679
WITH.

20:13.679 --> 20:15.815
I MEAN, THIS IS NOT LIKE CURING

20:15.815 --> 20:16.415
CANCER.

20:16.415 --> 20:18.184
THIS IS A VERY, VERY

20:18.184 --> 20:19.218
STRAIGHTFORWARD PROBLEM.

20:19.218 --> 20:20.486
IT'S A BILL.

20:20.486 --> 20:21.654
AND IN THE NORTHEAST AND MIDWEST

20:21.654 --> 20:22.922
STATES, THEY HAVE MORE MONEY TO

20:22.922 --> 20:23.856
WORK WITH THAN, SAY, IN THE

20:23.856 --> 20:24.857
SOUTH OR WESTERN STATES.

20:24.857 --> 20:25.891
>> Sreenivasan: OKAY, SO THIS

20:25.891 --> 20:26.892
GETS INTO A LITTLE BIT OF THE

20:26.892 --> 20:28.260
PHILOSOPHICAL QUESTION OF WHAT'S

20:28.260 --> 20:29.595
THE ROLE OF GOVERNMENT AND

20:29.595 --> 20:31.030
WHAT'S THE ROLE OF ASSISTANCE IN

20:31.030 --> 20:32.798
POVERTY, RIGHT?

20:32.798 --> 20:33.666
>> WELL, EXACTLY.

20:33.666 --> 20:36.035
IN A SENSE, THERE'S A BROAD

20:36.035 --> 20:39.638
AGREEMENT THAT PROGRAMS LIKE

20:39.638 --> 20:42.074
SNAP OR FOOD STAMPS, MEDICAID,

20:42.074 --> 20:43.375
THEY'RE ENTITLEMENT PROGRAMS IN

20:43.375 --> 20:44.543
THE SENSE THAT IF YOU'RE

20:44.543 --> 20:46.078
ELIGIBLE BASED ON INCOME, THERE

20:46.078 --> 20:47.713
WILL ALWAYS BE MONEY TO HELP

20:47.713 --> 20:48.414
YOU.

20:48.414 --> 20:50.382
ENERGY ASSISTANCE IS A

20:50.382 --> 20:51.650
DISCRETIONARY GRANT PROGRAM,

20:51.650 --> 20:52.318
WHICH MEANS THAT WHEN THE

20:52.318 --> 20:53.719
APPROPRIATION RUNS OUT, THE

20:53.719 --> 20:54.887
PROGRAM ENDS.

20:54.887 --> 20:56.689
SO THAT THERE'S A REAL

20:56.689 --> 20:57.423
DIFFERENCE.

20:57.423 --> 20:59.158
IT'S A SOCIETAL AGREEMENT TO

20:59.158 --> 21:00.426
HELP PEOPLE WITH FOOD, TO

21:00.426 --> 21:02.228
HELP OLD AGE... ELDERLY PEOPLE

21:02.228 --> 21:03.229
WITH SOCIAL SECURITY.

21:03.229 --> 21:05.397
THERE'S NOT A BROAD SOCIETAL

21:05.397 --> 21:06.532
AGREEMENT TO HELP PEOPLE WITH

21:06.532 --> 21:08.300
ENERGY, AND THAT'S THE REAL KEY

21:08.300 --> 21:09.435
DIFFERENCE.

21:09.435 --> 21:10.603
ONE OF THE OTHER DIFFERENCES IN

21:10.603 --> 21:11.637
ENERGY, THOUGH-- AND THIS IS

21:11.637 --> 21:14.073
WHERE I THINK WE GET INTO

21:14.073 --> 21:15.374
THIS SITUATION OF FAMILIES

21:15.374 --> 21:16.408
GETTING TO UNAFFORDABLE

21:16.408 --> 21:18.611
CASES-- IT'S NOT JUST THE

21:18.611 --> 21:20.279
PRICE OF ENERGY, IT'S ALSO

21:20.279 --> 21:21.614
HOW MUCH YOU USE.

21:21.614 --> 21:23.983
SO, IF THIS TURNS OUT... THIS

21:23.983 --> 21:25.618
WINTER TURNS OUT TO CONTINUE

21:25.618 --> 21:27.219
TO BE AS COLD AS IT IS, THEN

21:27.219 --> 21:28.587
FAMILIES WILL JUST NEED MORE

21:28.587 --> 21:29.789
MONEY TO PAY THEIR ENERGY

21:29.789 --> 21:31.290
BILL, AND THERE'S NOTHING TO

21:31.290 --> 21:32.258
HELP THEM.

21:32.258 --> 21:33.058
THAT'S THE PROBLEM.

21:33.058 --> 21:34.393
SO, THEY HAVE TO SUBSTITUTE.

21:34.393 --> 21:36.195
AND LOW-INCOME FAMILIES BUY

21:36.195 --> 21:38.164
LESS MEDICINE, LESS FOOD BECAUSE

21:38.164 --> 21:39.231
THEY HAVE TO PAY THEIR ENERGY

21:39.231 --> 21:39.999
BILL.

